<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00075</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING ALL BROADCAST MEDIA NETWORKS TO DEVOTE A TOTAL OF TWENTY (20) MINUTES OF REGULAR AIRTIME A DAY FOR PUBLIC SERVICE ANNOUNCEMENTS, FREE OF CHARGE, AND PROVIDING PENALTIES FOR THE VIOLATION THEREOF</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to require all broadcasting media networks to devote a total of twenty (20) minutes
of regular airtime a day for public service announcements (PSA) on various social issues
including but not limited to: 

 
1) Drug Abuse and Prevention; 
2) Policies and Laws; 
3) Road and Traffic Rules; 
4) Physical and Mental Health; 
5) Government Processes; 
6) Emergency Preparedness and Public Safety; 
7) Welfare Rights and Benefits; 
8) Environmental Issues; 
9) Education; 
10) Suicide Prevention; and 
11) Voter and Civic Education.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BARBERS, ROBERT ACE S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Paduano (000 2019-08-13)</td><td>2. Tambunting (000 2019-08-13)</td><tr><td>3. Co (E.) (000 2019-09-04)</td><td>4. Olivarez (000 2019-09-04)</td><tr><td>5. Kho (W.) (000 2019-09-18)</td><td>6. Agabas (000 2019-10-02)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC INFORMATION ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>